1:
Yahweh, rescue me from the wicked;
\q preserve me from violent men.
\q

2:
They plan evil in their hearts;
\q they cause battles every day.
\q

3:
Their tongues wound like serpents;
\q vipers' poison is on their lips.
\qs Selah\qs*

5:
The proud have set a trap for me;
\q they have spread a net;
\q they have set a snare for me.
\qs Selah\qs*

6:
I said to Yahweh, "You are my God;
\q listen to my cries for mercy."
\q

7:
Yahweh, my Lord, you are powerfully able to save me;
\q you shield my head in the day of battle.
\q

8:
Yahweh, do not grant the desires of the wicked;
\q do not let their plots succeed.
\qs Selah\qs*

9:
Those who surround me raise their heads;
\q let the mischief of their own lips cover them.
\q
